%% Feast Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as Feast Operator<br/>(controller-manager)
    participant FeastPod as Feast Deployment<br/>(online/offline/registry/UI)
    participant MLApp as ML Application
    participant Notebook as Kubeflow Notebook<br/>(feast-integration labeled)
    participant CronJob as CronJob Pod
    participant DB as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant ObjStore as S3/GCS<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User, ObjStore: Flow 1: FeatureStore Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: Create FeatureStore CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch Event notification<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Services,<br/>ConfigMaps, PVCs, RBAC,<br/>CronJob, Route (OCP)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update FeatureStore status<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>User: FeatureStore ready

    Note over MLApp, DB: Flow 2: Feature Retrieval (Online Store)
    MLApp->>FeastPod: gRPC get_online_features<br/>Port: 80/443 TCP<br/>Encryption: TLS (if configured)<br/>Auth: K8s RBAC / OIDC / None
    FeastPod->>DB: Query features<br/>Port: 5432/TCP<br/>Encryption: TLS (optional)<br/>Auth: Secret credentials
    DB-->>FeastPod: Feature data
    FeastPod-->>MLApp: Feature response (gRPC)

    Note over Notebook, Operator: Flow 3: Notebook Feast Integration
    User->>K8sAPI: Label Notebook with<br/>opendatahub.io/feast-integration=true
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Notebook watch event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create {notebook-name}-feast-config<br/>ConfigMap (feature_store.yaml)
    Notebook->>FeastPod: Connect to Feast services<br/>Port: 80/443 TCP<br/>gRPC/HTTP<br/>Auth: per config

    Note over CronJob, DB: Flow 4: CronJob Materialization
    CronJob->>FeastPod: kubectl exec<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount (RBAC)
    FeastPod->>FeastPod: feast apply
    FeastPod->>FeastPod: feast materialize-incremental
    FeastPod->>DB: Materialize features<br/>Port: 5432/TCP<br/>Auth: Secret credentials
    FeastPod->>ObjStore: Persist registry<br/>Port: 443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: IAM/Secret
